1:
Then Moses and the people of Israel sang this song to Yahweh. They sang,\q "I will sing to Yahweh, for he has triumphed gloriously;
\q the horse and its rider he has thrown into the sea.


\q

8:
By the blast of your nostrils the waters were piled up;\q the flowing waters stood upright in a heap;
\q the deep water was congealed in the heart of the sea.


\q

9:
The enemy said, 'I will pursue, I will overtake, I will share out the plunder;\q my desire will be satisfied on them;
\q I will draw my sword; my hand will destroy them.'
\q

15:
Then the chiefs of Edom will fear;\q the soldiers of Moab will shake;
\q all the inhabitants of Canaan will melt away.


\q
